## How It Works

1. **Client-Side Integration**: The `<SpeedInsights />` component is rendered as part of the React application
2. **Automatic Tracking**: Once deployed to Vercel, the component will automatically inject the Speed Insights script
3. **Route Tracking**: For React applications, the component automatically tracks route changes
4. **Performance Metrics**: Collects Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS, TTFB, FCP, INP)

## Next Steps for Deployment

To complete the Speed Insights setup:

1. **Enable in Vercel Dashboard**:
   - Go to your Vercel project dashboard
   - Navigate to the "Speed Insights" tab
   - Click "Enable" to activate the feature

2. **Deploy to Vercel**:
   ```bash
   vercel deploy
   ```
   Or connect your git repository for automatic deployments

3. **Verify Installation**:
   - After deployment, check for `/_vercel/speed-insights/script.js` in your page source
   - The Speed Insights routes will be available at `/_vercel/speed-insights/*`

4. **View Data**:
   - Data will appear in the Vercel dashboard after users visit your site
   - Allow a few days for meaningful metrics to accumulate

## Implementation Choice Rationale

**Why this approach:**
- ✅ Uses the official `@vercel/speed-insights/react` package for seamless React integration
